  "text": "## Apache Kafka Consumer Offset Management Architecture\n\nThe consumer offset management in Apache Kafka is implemented through a multi-layer architecture:\n\n### 1. **OffsetAndMetadata Storage**\n\nKafka maintains two key classes for offset metadata:\n- **Client-side**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java` - Used by consumers to track committed offsets\n- **Server-side**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetAndMetadata.java` - Server representation of committed offsets with epoch information\n\nThese classes store the committed offset, optional metadata string, commit timestamp, and optional expiration timestamp.\n\n### 2. **GroupCoordinator Offset Commit Handler**\n\nThe offset commit workflow is orchestrated through:\n- **GroupCoordinator Interface**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java` - Defines commitOffsets, fetchOffsets, and deleteOffsets contract\n- **GroupCoordinatorService**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java` - Implements the coordinator interface with commitOffsets method\n- **GroupCoordinatorShard**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java` - Handles per-shard offset commit operations\n\n### 3. **OffsetFetch Request Processor**\n\nOffset fetching is handled through request/response classes:\n- **OffsetFetchRequest**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchRequest.java` - Client request to fetch committed offsets\n- **OffsetFetchResponse**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchResponse.java` - Server response with offset data\n- **OffsetMetadataManager**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java` - Core manager implementing fetchOffsets logic\n\n### 4. **Offset Commit Management**\n\nOffset commit operations are implemented through:\n- **OffsetCommitRequest**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitRequest.java`\n- **OffsetCommitResponse**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitResponse.java`\n- **OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffsets()**: Core implementation in `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java`\n- **CommitRequestManager**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CommitRequestManager.java` - Client-side offset commit orchestration\n- **ConsumerCoordinator**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java` - Legacy client-side coordinator\n\n### 5. **__consumer_offsets Topic Storage**\n\nOffsets are persisted in the `__consumer_offsets` compacted topic using:\n- **OffsetCommitKey**: Generated from `group-coordinator/src/main/resources/common/message/OffsetCommitKey.json` - Key format for offset records\n- **GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java` - Creates offset commit records\n- **GroupCoordinatorRecordSerde**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordSerde.java` - Serialization logic\n- **GroupMetadataManager**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java` - Manages group state persistence\n\n### 6. **Offset Deletion & Management**\n\nOffset deletion is handled through:\n- **OffsetDeleteRequest**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetDeleteRequest.java`\n- **OffsetMetadataManager.deleteOffsets()**: Deletion implementation\n\n### 7. **Transactional Offset Commits**\n\nTransactional operations on offsets use:\n- **TxnOffsetCommitRequest**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/TxnOffsetCommitRequest.java`\n- **TxnOffsetCommitResponse**: `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/TxnOffsetCommitResponse.java`\n\n### 8. **Group Implementations**\n\nDifferent group types manage offsets through their implementations:\n- **ClassicGroup**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroup.java` - Legacy group offset validation\n- **ConsumerGroup**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroup.java` - Modern consumer group\n- **ShareGroup**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/share/ShareGroup.java` - Share group offset management\n- **StreamsGroup**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/streams/StreamsGroup.java` - Streams group\n\n### 9. **Request Handling**\n\nAll offset-related requests are dispatched through:\n- **KafkaApis**: `core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala` - Contains handleOffsetCommitRequest, handleOffsetFetchRequest, handleOffsetDeleteRequest, and handleTxnOffsetCommitRequest methods\n\n### 10. **Configuration**\n\nOffset management behavior is controlled through:\n- **GroupCoordinatorConfig**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorConfig.java` - Configuration for offsets topic partitions, replication factor, offset metadata max size, offset load buffer size, etc.\n\nThe architecture uses a snapshot registry pattern for point-in-time consistent offset views, and the __consumer_offsets topic uses log compaction to maintain only the latest offset for each group-partition pair."
}

